Your starting health is equal to 4 + your Con bonus. Re-calculate your health only when receiving a
permanent modifier to Con.

Your Evasion bonus is equal to 2 + Spd - Size. If your Dex is greater than 1, add one to your Evd. If your Dex is less than -1, subtract one from your Evd. Recalculate whenever your
Spd, Dex, or Size changes, even temporarily.

Pick an occupation; this is what your character did for a living before becoming
an adventurer (sailor, blacksmith, farmer, shepherd, etc.).

Your character can speak the Common tongue and the language of your race. If
your Int bonus is +2 or higher, you know an additional language, or two
languages if your Int is +4 or higher.

If your Cha bonus is +3 or higher, you know another language.

[section 1 Luck]

Sometimes, you may be asked to see if you are Lucky or not. To see if you're Lucky, roll 1d6. If the result is a 5 or 6, you are Lucky.

[section 1 Attribute Drain]

For each point of attribute drain that you suffer, temporarily reduce the bonus
of that attribute by one. Attribute drain never changes your total health, but
does change your Mv and Evd.

If one of your attributes is reduced to -4, you suffer from the corresponding
effect.
