[section 2 Bards]

Bards are proficient with weapons up to d6 and armor up to type 3.

You have a number of saga points equal to your Cha + the number of languages that you know.

You may spend one saga point as part of a performance to give any creatures that can
understand you and that listen for at least five minutes a +1 to any one attribute for one hour.

You may spend one saga point to begin a performance that fascinates any number of creatures that can hear and understand you. A successful [check cha cha] prevents fascination; a hostile creature only fails on a roll of 1. While fascinated, the creature pays no attention to anything except your performance. The fascination lasts until you end your performance, another creature takes an action to shake
a fascinated creature out of your spell, or if the fascinated creature is attacked.

You may also spend one saga point at any time to give a creature that can hear and understand
you a +1 or -1 to any roll.

